em For $t^2 \\neq 1$ then $LH_n \\cong SP_n$ at least up to rank$n=7$\n(for $t=-1$ they are not isomorphic for $n>2$; for $t=1$ they are not\nisomorphic for $n>1$).\n  Finally we discuss a number of other intriguing points arising from this\nconstruction in topology, representation theory and combinatorics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Aug 2020 16:40:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 18:21:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-31"}
