 nodes, the more similar their embedding vectors in the latent\nrepresentation space will be. The results of our experiments on several\nreal-world datasets demonstrate that the proposed MulCEV framework markedly\noutperforms current embedding-based methods, especially when the number of\ntraining iterations is small.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Aug 2020 10:04:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Aug 2020 01:56:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 9 Nov 2021 12:36:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-10"}
