 losses of orbital\nenergy. These effects combine, giving rise to a large variation in the ratio of\nsequent apocentres for accreted systems. We find that, within 2 virial radii\nfrom host centres, the concentrations of first-infall halos are remarkably\nsimilar those of isolated field halos, whereas backsplash haloes, as well as\nsystems that were pre-processed, are considerably more concentrated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Aug 2020 15:47:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Jan 2021 05:07:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-08"}
